channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: French judge extends police custody for Telegram CEO Pavel Durov
item.description: French prosecutors say an investigative judge has extended police custody for the Telegram CEO, Pavel Durov

item.title: Ask an Advisor: With $1 Million, How Can I Maximize Passive Income and Cut Taxes?
Bronfman withdraws bid for Paramount, clearing path for Skydance merger
item.description: The merger between entertainment giant Paramount and media company Skydance is set to go ahead after Edgar Bronfman Jr. withdrew a competing offer.

item.title: Man drowns after pushing 2 kids to safety from strong river currents
item.description: A 39-year-old man has drowned after pushing two children to safety from a river before succumbing to the current himself, officials said.

item.title: Keir Starmer warns autumn budget will be ‘painful’
Zuckerberg vows to resist federal efforts to influence Meta's content
item.description: Meta CEO Mark Zuckerberg says federal pressure on his social media platforms to take down certain COVID-19 content in 2021 was "wrong," and he'd resist similar attempts in the future.

item.title: Authorities arrest ex-sheriff’s deputy who fatally shot a Black airman at his home
item.description: Authorities have arrested a former Florida sheriff’s deputy charged with killing a Black U.S. Air Force senior airman who answered his apartment door while holding a gun pointed toward the ground

item.title: Zuckerberg says Biden administration pressured Meta to censor COVID-19 content
U.S. open to escorting Philippine ships amid clashes with China
item.description: American warships could escort Philippine vessels in the disputed South China Sea amid increasing confrontations with China, U.S. commander says.

item.title: Russia launches 'nightmare' deadly drone and missile strikes in Ukraine, Kyiv says
item.description: At least 15 regions throughout Ukraine had been struck in the early morning attack, Kira Rudick, a member of Ukrainian Parliament, said on Monday.

item.title: Bear Caught on Camera Taking Dip in Hot Tub
7 community guards killed by cartel, 7 others kidnapped in Mexico
item.description: Seven guards were killed just days after seven members of a community police force were kidnapped, apparently by cartel gunmen.

item.title: WATCH: Amusement park ride passengers stranded during storm
item.description: Six Flags Mexico park guests were stuck dangling on a ride as a storm rolled through, temporarily halting service. They were stuck for 10 minutes before being safely let off the ride.

item.title: ‘The ocean is overflowing’: UN chief issues global SOS as new reports warn Pacific sea-level rise outstrips global average
Dems sue over Georgia rules they say could block election certifications
item.description: The state and national Democratic parties have to try to block two recent rules adopted by Georgia's State Election Board they say could be used by county officials to refuse to certify elections.
